<HEADLINE>
<P>
JOHN J. POLLON; SERVED ON CITY AND COUNTY PANELS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 John J. Pollon, 83, who served on the Los Angeles County Housing Authority and 
the city Planning Commission through much of the 1960s.From 1967 to 1971 he was 
commission president, resigning in 1971 in a policy dispute. Pollon was also 
active in youth sports organizations and conservation groups and was a director 
of City National Bank of Beverly Hills. In Tarzana on Sept. 22 of cancer. 
</P>
