<HEADLINE>
<P>
TECHNOWATCH: YOU'LL LOOK SWEET, UPON THE SEAT . . . 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNN SIMROSS, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bicycles built for two sure aren't what they used to be, which was heavy, hard 
to ride and difficult to store. Now there's the Montague TriFrame Tandem, an 
8-foot tandem bike that can be folded and carried in a 3-foot case. 
</P>
<P>
 This unusual two-person model is a full-size high-performance bicycle that 
folds easily in several minutes with quick release levers (no tools needed) and 
fits in the trunk or back seat of a car. Or it can be transported on trains or 
airplanes. 
</P>
<P>
 The TriFrame Tandem weighs 47.8 pounds and is constructed of steel tubes 
within tubes to form a sturdy frame. It has a 21-speed shifting system, which, 
when the rider turns the handlebar grip, automatically shifts into the next 
gear. 
</P>
<P>
 The bicycle is an excellent solution for urban couples who want to exercise 
together but have no place to store an ordinary tandem bike. 
</P>
<P>
 Montague Corp. President David Montague says tandem bikes have recently become 
popular because "they allow two people of different exercise levels to ride 
together. One person can compensate for the other." 
</P>
<P>
 The company also makes several models of mountain bikes and cross bikes that 
fold. 
</P>
<P>
 The TriFrame Tandem ($1,995) can be ordered from Montague Corp. at (800) 
736-5348. 
</P>
<P>
 An optional accessory is the Airliner Travel System ($599), which includes a 
hard-shell carrying case, special tube pads that wrap around the frame to 
protect it, Velcro-like tie-down straps and three nylon bags in which to store 
helmets, seats and other biking equipment. New Sanyo Fax Machine Is a Small 
Production 
</P>
<P>
 In October, Sanyo introduces its new facsimile machine, SFX-P50, a compact 
model ideal for home offices. The ink-jet fax uses plain paper and can send and 
receive faxes simultaneously. 
</P>
<P>
 SFX-P50 is 13 inches by 8 inches, so it takes up little space on a desk. It 
transmits a letter-size document in about nine seconds, and also has a timed 
transmission feature that makes it possible to automatically send up to 20 
pages to 50 people. 
</P>
<P>
 The unit has a 10-sheet automatic document feeder and a two-line, 32-digit LCD 
display so you can read both the name and phone number of the person or company 
being contacted. 
</P>
<P>
 SFX-P50 ($1,395) will be available nationwide next month at Circuit City and 
the Good Guys stores. Clean Tap Water, Courtesy of a Filtering Straw 
</P>
<P>
 The Clean Sip Water Filter Drinking Straw can provide clean, odor-free tap 
water wherever you are. Its two-part replaceable filter -- one is copper, zinc 
and alloy; the other, granulated charcoal -- removes bacteria, chlorine, 
sediment, lead and algae. 
</P>
<P>
 The 8 1/2-inch plastic straw comes with its own carrying case, handy for 
travelers, kids at school, bikers, boaters and campers. The filtering straw 
also fits in most sports bottles. It should last about a year before you need 
replacement filters.  
</P>
<P>
 Clean Sip ($14.95 including shipping and handling) can be ordered from the 
J.M. Glennon Co., 9124 N.E. 141st St., Bothell, Wash. 98011; (800) 796-6773, 
Ext. 512. A set of replacement filters costs $10. Allow two weeks for delivery. 
</P>
</TEXT>
