<TEXT>
<P>
 Tonight's featured race at Los Alamitos, the $20,000 Vandy's Flash Handicap, 
has drawn a tougher field than the $20,000 purse would indicate. 
</P>
<P>
 Heza Fast Man, a talented 3-year-old colt trained by John Bassett, will be 
making his 1994 Los Alamitos debut in the race. The colt won last year's Texas 
Classic Futurity, ran a close second in the All-American Futurity behind A 
Classic Dash and finished second in the All-American Derby this year. 
</P>
<P>
 Ridden by Henry Garcia, Heza Fast Man faces a tough field that includes Los 
Alamitos stakes winners Daily Triple, Rainbow Sun, Sticky N Picky, Lil Bita 
Brunch, Assured Dash and Time For Royal Cash. STACY PIGOTT 
