PREP FOOTBALL; HAYNES HELPS VILLA PARK SHUT OUT LOARA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON CLIFFORD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sophomore Franklin Haynes intercepted three passes and scored two touchdowns 
to help lead No. 9 Villa Park to a 35-0 victory over Loara Thursday night at El 
Modena High School. 
</P>
<P>
 Quarterback Sean McMahon led the Spartans on offense, completing six of nine 
passes for 173 yards and three touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 Villa Park held Loara (0-4) to 132 yards in total offense, including 39 on the 
ground. 
</P>
<P>
 Two quick touchdown passes in the first quarter opened the scoring for the 
Spartans (3-0-1). 
</P>
<P>
 McMahon hit Kris Fisher on an 18-yard scoring pass and, on his next attempt, 
McMahon found Sam Stremick for a 67-yard score to help Villa Park to a 14-0 
halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
 The Spartans controlled the momentum throughout the second half, starting with 
the kickoff. 
</P>
<P>
 Haynes returned the kick 83 yards for his first score. On the Spartans' next 
possession, McMahon connected on his third touchdown, a 23-yard pass to Fisher, 
giving Villa Park a 28-0 lead midway through the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Haynes capped the scoring when he intercepted his third pass of the night and 
returned it 45 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Tony D'Amato had 59 yards in six carries for the Spartans. 
</P>
<P>
 Loara quarterback Jim Kirkland completed eight of 22 for 65 yards and three 
interceptions. JON CLIFFORD 
</P>
