<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP FOOTBALL; OCEAN VIEW GETS CLOSE BEFORE LOSING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Estancia's winning streak continued, as did Ocean View's losing streak, as the 
Eagles won, 14-3, in a nonleague football game Thursday at Newport Harbor High. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the third consecutive victory for Estancia (3-1), after a nine-game 
losing streak.Ocean View (0-4) has lost 33 in a row, the longest streak in 
California. 
</P>
<P>
 Ocean View still had a chance in the fourth quarter but failed on a fourth 
down at the Estancia 20. The drive had already been helped by three 15-yard 
penalties against Estancia. 
</P>
<P>
 Ocean View faced a fourth and one when quarterback Ted Norman faked a handoff 
inside and started a bootleg to the left. But Estancia defensive back Karlo 
Amaya read the play and tackled Norman for a three-yard loss. 
</P>
<P>
 Estancia then went on a 14-play drive but faced a key fourth-down play of its 
own. 
</P>
<P>
 The Eagles were on the Ocean View one with 1 minute 49 seconds left, leading, 
7-3. Instead of going for the field goal, Estancia Coach John Liebengood 
elected to try for the touchdown. Oscar Lomeli, behind a strong surge of the 
offensive line, scored with ease. 
</P>
<P>
 Lomeli finished with 70 yards in 13 carries and teammate Bachy Gonzalez had a 
game-high 106 yards in 19 attempts. 
</P>
<P>
 "The bottom line is the win," Liebengood said. "We've just got to keep 
building because our toughest games are ahead." 
</P>
<P>
 Ocean View appeared headed to the locker room at halftime with a 3-0 lead only 
to have disaster strike. Jon Dempsey kicked a 21-yard field goal with 11 
seconds left in the half. 
</P>
<P>
 But Estancia's Chris Felix took the following kickoff and cut to the left 
sideline and finished with a 76-yard return for a touchdown. STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
