<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; CORBIN LEADS NO. 1 IRVINE PAST NO. 3 EL TORO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MELANIE NEFF 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Top-ranked Irvine continued its quest to repeat as Division I State champion, 
defeating No. 3 El Toro, 17-38, in girls' cross-country Thursday at Irvine 
High. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine's Jessica Corbin surprised no one, taking an early lead and breezing to 
a first-place finish.Corbin, competing in her second meet since recovering from 
a hip injury, finished the three-mile race in 18 minutes 1 second. 
</P>
<P>
 The Vaqueros (2-0) took five of the top six spots. Anna-Kaisa Niemi finished 
second in 18:33 and Erin Livermore took third in 18:41. 
</P>
<P>
 "I was thrilled with our performance," Vaquero Coach Randy Rossi said. "I was 
very impressed with the way the girls ran their race."  
</P>
<P>
 Stacey Roberson was the top finisher for the Chargers (1-1), finishing fourth 
in 19:02. 
</P>
<P>
 In the boys' race, El Toro (2-0) easily defeated Irvine (0-2), 19-44. The 
Chargers' John Glover won in 16:09. Irvine's Justin Nyberg finished right 
behind Glover in 16:13. The next six spots belonged to El Toro. 
</P>
<P>
 El Toro's Martin Pennell, in his first race after a car accident which put him 
and teammate Tomas Mejia in the hospital, took fifth place in 16:27. Mejia 
remains hospitalized in a coma. MELANIE NEFF 
</P>
</TEXT>
