<P>
EXECUTIVE SUITE: COMPANY TOWN; FAMILY CHANNEL FILLS POSTS IN AFFILIATE 
RELATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Family Channel made a number of appointments in its affiliate relations 
area. Mark Solow will handle Southwest affiliate relations; Clay Boudreax, 
mid-South; Janelle L. Slipp, West; Tim J. Kassick, Rocky Mountain region; Tim 
Larson, Midwest; Chip Fortier, Southeast; Stan Majkut, mid-Atlantic, and Don 
Scott, Northeast. 
</P>
<P>
 * Falcon Holding Group said Jon Lunsford has been named vice president of 
finance and corporate development. 
</P>
<P>
 * Martyn S. Weinberg has been named president and chief operating officer of 
Pacific Rim Entertainment. 
</P>
<P>
 * Matthew McMarthy has been named executive producer of "Marilu," a new talk 
show hosted by actress Marilu Henner. 
</P>
<P>
 * Ralph Leshansky has been named vice president of theatrical sales for 
Channel M, a video network in shopping malls. 
</P>
<P>
 * Former New York magazine Publisher Richard Kinsler has joined Playboy 
Enterprises as executive vice president of the publishing group and publisher 
of Playboy magazine. 
</P>
<P>
 * Entertainment marketing executives Denise Battaglia and Michael Pacelli have 
joined the Eisaman, Johns & Laws advertising agency. 
</P>
<P>
 * Michael G. Martinez has been named vice president and general manager of 
KVEA-TV Channel 52. 
</P>
<P>
 * AMC Entertainment has promoted James Beynon to vice president and treasurer. 
</P>
<P>
 * MTV Latino has promoted Damaris Valero to vice president of sales. 
</P>
<P>
 * Wayne Lepoff has been named chief executive of New World's Genesis 
Entertainment unit. 
</P>
<P>
 * Herbert N. Dorfman has been named president of Orion Home Entertainment 
Corp. 
</P>
<P>
 * Nelvana Communications has promoted Lara Stein to manager of domestic 
licensing. 
</P>
<P>
 * Hal G. Rosenbluth has been promoted to president and chief operating officer 
of Kaufman Astoria Studios in New York. 
</P>
