<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSMAKERS: PACIFIC SCIENTIFIC CO. APPOINTS PRESIDENT OF 
INSTRUMENTS DIVISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Joseph R. Monkowski has been appointed president of the instruments division 
of Pacific Scientific Co., a Newport Beach manufacturer of electrical and 
safety equipment. He succeeds Robert L. Olsen, who remains a consultant to the 
company. Monkowski previously held positions with Photon Dynamics Inc., Lam 
Research Corp., and Schumacher Co. He was also chairman and president of 
Monkowski-Rhine Inc., which was bought by Lam Research. 
</P>
<P>
 * Kenneth T. Sipiora has been appointed a senior vice president of Marsh & 
McLennan Inc. in the Newport Beach office. He had been sales manager in the 
insurance brokerage's Indianapolis office before transferring to the Newport 
Beach office in 1993. Before that, Sipiora was a property and casualty broker 
in the Midwest for 16 years. 
</P>
<P>
 * Ernest J. Casarez has formed Casarez & Associates, a Lake Forest consulting 
firm. He had been president of Cornerstone Bank in Mission Viejo since its 
formation in 1983. Before that, Casarez was assistant manager of the Latin 
American division for Bank of America. 
</P>
<P>
 * Kim Carino has been appointed to the newly created position of director of 
merchandising for Interplay Productions Inc., an Irvine entertainment software 
company. Before joining Interplay in 1991, she held marketing positions with 
Mattel Toys and Tomy Toys. Carino also directed marketing and licensing at the 
Corinthia Group, an independent record label. 
</P>
<P>
 * Bob Furtado has been named senior vice president of operations for Ingram 
Micro Inc., a Santa Ana wholesale distributor of microcomputer products. 
Furtado was named vice president of operations for Ingram Micro in 1989. In 
addition, Alain Maquet has been appointed vice president of Southern European 
operations, and Erik van Netten was appointed vice president of Northern 
European operations. Maquet joined the company in 1993 as managing director of 
Ingram Micro France. Van Netten joined Ingram Micro in 1993 as managing 
director of the Netherlands operation through the acquisition of the Trend 
Group, where he was owner and president. 
</P>
<P>
 * John Wheeler has been appointed to the newly created position of chief 
operating officer for Security Environmental Systems Inc., a Huntington Beach 
waste management, remediation and transportation services company. Wheeler was 
formerly president of two hazardous waste treatment facilities in the Midwest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
