</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In its final football game as a member of the California Collegiate Athletic 
Assn. in 1981, Cal State Northridge defeated defending NCAA Division II 
champion Cal Poly San Luis Obispo, 32-14, to win the conference championship. 
Northridge joined the Western Football Conference the following season. 
