<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRIAL HIGHLIGHTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A look at some of the key events in the murder trial of O.J. Simpson on 
Thursday: 
</P>
<P>
 * Summary: Superior Court Judge Lance A. Ito gave the final group of 
prospective jurors detailed questionnaires probing their views on an array of 
topics that might be relevant to the trial. A total of 304 prospective jurors 
have completed the documents and are expected to begin undergoing questioning 
by Ito and the lawyers starting Oct. 12. 
</P>
<P>
 * Court action: A defense motion opposing sequestration of the jury was 
unsealed. In it, Simpson's lawyers cite the "folklore that a sequestered jury 
is a convicting jury." 
</P>
<P>
 * Outside the court: Scores of television crews that have set up outside the 
Criminal Courts Building temporarily pulled out of their encampments. No more 
hearings in the Simpson case are scheduled until Wednesday. 
</P>
