<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: LA HABRA; POLICE IN SEARCH OF DRUGS FIND UNEXPLODED BOMB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DEBBIE KONG 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police serving a search warrant for narcotics and paraphernalia Thursday were 
surprised to find an unexploded smoke bomb instead. 
</P>
<P>
 Although police did not find any of the suspected methamphetamine, they 
arrested Brian E. Bales, 37, of La Habra, on suspicion of possessing narcotic 
paraphernalia and a deadly weapon, said La Habra Lt. Wayne Lowry.Bales was 
being held in La Habra City Jail Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Narcotics paraphernalia can include smoking, weighing or illegal injection 
devices. Lowry would not specify what paraphernalia or weapon Bales allegedly 
possessed. 
</P>
<P>
 Two men and one woman in the house in the 1500 the block of Sheffield Street, 
a single-family residential area, were evacuated at about 7 a.m. when officers 
found a box labeled "grenade."  
</P>
<P>
 Police called in the Orange County Sheriff's Department bomb squad, which 
removed the box, examined it and took it away to be destroyed. The smoke bomb 
did not go off. No one was injured.DEBBIE KONG 
</P>
</TEXT>
