COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: LOS ALAMITOS; ORDINANCE TO GOVERN SALE OF HOLIDAY ITEMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Selling Halloween pumpkins and Christmas trees will be allowed only on certain 
dates under an ordinance tentatively approved by the City Council this week. 
</P>
<P>
 The ordinance also provides that vendors must obtain, in addition to a 
business license, a $75 permit to sell the seasonal items.Pumpkins may be sold 
from Saturday to Oct. 31 and Christmas trees from the day after Thanksgiving to 
Dec. 25. 
</P>
<P>
 Nonprofit groups are exempt from paying for the permit, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Community development director Elizabeth Binsack said the ordinance will 
enable the Planning Department to process permit applications on time and apply 
consistent standards. 
</P>
<P>
 The $75 fee, the same amount currently charged, allows the permit holder to 
sell both pumpkins and Christmas trees in the same year.BERT ELJERA 
