<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN DIED TRYING TO HURT OFFICERS, POLICE SAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two police detectives conducting a surveillance near Musial Street and 
McCormack Lane Thursday shot and fatally wounded a suspect who tried to run 
over the approaching officers, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 About 1:30 p.m., officers "in the process of making contact" with the suspect 
fired their weapons at the 24-year-old man, who has not been identified, 
according to Placentia Lt. Chuck Babcock.The suspect was pronounced dead at 
Placentia Linda Hospital, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police would not say what the surveillance was about nor what the man was 
suspected of. 
</P>
<P>
 He was alone in his vehicle at the time of the shooting, and no other suspects 
were arrested. 
</P>
<P>
 As in all officer-involved shootings, the man's death is being investigated by 
the Orange County district attorney's office. 
</P>
