<P>
 Piper Jaffray Again Sued Over Derivatives Losses: The investment company is 
being sued for losses in a mutual fund it manages for Managers Funds of 
Norwalk, Conn. Lawyers for nine investors in Alabama, Kansas, Maryland and 
Florida filed the lawsuit in U.S. District Court in Minneapolis, where the firm 
is based, claiming they were misled about the fund's investment policies and 
its potential volatility. It is the 11th lawsuit to be filed against Piper 
Jaffray Inc. for derivative-related losses. 
</P>
