<P>
BRIEFLY: LABOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Wilson Rescinds Overtime Waiver: The emergency waiver of a state overtime 
requirement had been issued to relieve traffic congestion after the Jan. 17 
Northridge earthquake. Gov. Pete Wilson asked the Legislature to pass new 
legislation that would permanently repeal the state's daily overtime 
provision.The existing law requires employers to pay workers overtime whenever 
they work more than eight hours in a day. Wilson exempted Southland employers 
from the requirement after the quake as a way to encourage flexible work 
schedules. He said he rescinded the waiver because emergency conditions no 
longer exist in the Southland, but he encouraged lawmakers to permanently 
repeal the requirement to accommodate the needs of both employers and 
employees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
