<TEXT>
<P>
 GM Strike Continues: Bargainers were unable to find a compromise that could 
end the potentially crippling strike against General Motors Corp. Dave Yettaw, 
president of United Auto Workers Local 599, said the two sides would meet again 
today. The strike by 11,500 GM workers at the 123-acre Buick City complex in 
Flint, Mich., led to the closing of two plants in Lansing, Mich., on Tuesday, 
the first day of the strike, and threatened to lead to the closings of others. 
Thousands of workers in other GM plants have been told not to report to work 
today or Saturday. 
</P>
