<BYLINE>
<P>
By DEBORA VRANA, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Metalclad Corp.: The firm said Thursday that it had raised $6.9 million 
through a private placement of 2.3 million shares of its stock with 20 European 
institutional investors. 
</P>
<P>
 The placement gives Metalclad's new investors a 17% stake in the Newport Beach 
company. 
</P>
<P>
 The company, which develops hazardous waste treatment facilities in Mexico, 
said that it will use the proceeds to expand its Mexican subsidiary, Quimica 
Omega, by opening nine new offices in that country by March, 1995. 
</P>
