 Won the job midway through last season and kept the Ducks competitive when 
occasionally all else failed. Saw first extensive NHL action last season, 
posting a 20-27-3 record with an impressive 2.83 goals-against average. Stopped 
38 shots against Toronto in team's first shutout. 
